<ManSection>
  <Attr Arg="V" Name="EmbeddingDimension" Label="for IsVanishingSet"/>
 <Returns>a non-negative integer
</Returns>
 <Description>
The argument is a vanishingSet <Math>V</Math>. We then return the embedding dimension of this vanishing set.
 </Description>
</ManSection>


<ManSection>
  <Attr Arg="V" Name="CohomologicalIndex" Label="for IsVanishingSet"/>
 <Returns>an integer between <Math>0</Math> and <Math>dim \left( X_\Sigma \right)</Math>
</Returns>
 <Description>
The argument is a vanishingSet <Math>V</Math>. This vanishing set identifies those <Math>D \in Pic \left( X_\Sigma \right)</Math>
such that <Math>H^i \left( X_\Sigma, \mathcal{O} \left( D \right) \right) = 0</Math>. We return the integer <Math>i</Math>.
 </Description>
</ManSection>


<ManSection>
  <Attr Arg="V" Name="CohomologicalSpecification" Label="for IsVanishingSet"/>
 <Returns>a string
</Returns>
 <Description>
The argument is a vanishingSet <Math>V</Math>. This could for example identify those <Math>D \in Pic \left( X_\Sigma \right)</Math>
such that <Math>H^i \left( X_\Sigma, \mathcal{O} \left( D \right) \right) = 0</Math> for all <Math>i > 0</Math>.
If such a specification is known, it will be returned by this method.
 </Description>
</ManSection>


<ManSection>
  <Attr Arg="V" Name="AmbientToricVariety" Label="for IsVanishingSet"/>
 <Description>
The argument is a vanishingSet <Math>V</Math>. We return the toric variety to which this vanishing set belongs.
 </Description>
